# Deprecation policy

## Types

| Type | Semver | Example |
|------|--------|---------|
| **Deprecation warning** | Minor — existing API still works, emit console.warn | Rename `$scroll.locked()` → `$scroll.isLocked` |
| **Removal** | Major — API no longer available | Remove `$scroll.locked()` entirely |
| **Renaming** | Major — old name removed | `$jsonapi` magic renamed |

## Rules

1. Deprecations MUST be announced in CHANGELOG.md with migration path.
2. Deprecated APIs MUST emit `console.warn` at first use.
3. Deprecated APIs MUST include `@deprecated` JSDoc tag.
4. Deprecated APIs MUST be removed in a `major` bump, never `patch`.
5. Documentation MUST NOT be removed for deprecated APIs until removal.

## Migration pattern

```typescript
// Deprecated API
export function legacyMethod(): void {
  console.warn(
    "[alpine-toolkit] legacyMethod() is deprecated. Use newMethod() instead.",
  );
  return newMethod();
}

// New API
export function newMethod(): void {
  // actual implementation
}
```

## Changelog entry format

```markdown
### Deprecated

- `$scroll.locked()` → use `$scroll.isLocked` (getter, no parentheses) — [#1234](link)

### Removed (Major only)

- `$scroll.locked()` — use `$scroll.isLocked` instead — [#1234](link)
```
